# Dictate Context

This file is prepended to every LLM cleanup call. Keep it under ~400 tokens (~1600 chars).
Copy this to ~/.config/dictate/context.md and personalize it.

## Vocabulary (stable — update rarely)

Proper nouns and tools that voice transcription commonly mangles:

- Claude (not "Cloud") — AI assistant by Anthropic; also Claude Code (the CLI)
- Cursor — AI code editor (not "cursor" the mouse pointer)
- <YourCompany> — your company name (add any common transcription errors here)
- <YourTeam> — your team name (e.g., "not 'surcharge team' but 'SuperCharged Team'")
- LiteLLM — open-source LLM proxy toolkit (not "light LLM" or "little LLM")
- mlx-whisper — on-device transcription tool (not "MLX whisper" or "mix whisper")
- GitLab / GitHub — version control platforms (not "get lab" or "git lab")

## Current Focus (ephemeral — update weekly or as projects shift)

Active projects and context to help the cleanup LLM understand references:

- Working on: <your current project or feature>
- Key repos: <your main repos>
- Team: <your team name>

<!-- Update the Current Focus section regularly. The Vocabulary section rarely needs changes. -->
